		<title>A Sequel to THE TIME MACHINE?</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/andy-robertson-s-night-land-essays/1-a-sequel-to-the-time-machine"/>
		<published>2015-04-19T01:22:07+00:00</published>
		<updated>2015-04-19T01:22:07+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/andy-robertson-s-night-land-essays/1-a-sequel-to-the-time-machine</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;The Science-Fictional Underpinning of THE NIGHT LAND&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/1-a-sequel-to-the-time-machine&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-dying-earth-horror-irrational-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;beaten brass rings and a wrought iron spike spiralling down into the center of an orange vortex.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;article-teaser&quot;&gt;The Night Land is typically assumed to be either a work of fantasy, or one of horror. I will argue that it is Science Fiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;The Science-Fictional Underpinning of THE NIGHT LAND&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/1-a-sequel-to-the-time-machine&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/coady-dying-earth-horror-irrational-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;beaten brass rings and a wrought iron spike spiralling down into the center of an orange vortex.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;article-teaser&quot;&gt;The Night Land is typically assumed to be either a work of fantasy, or one of horror. I will argue that it is Science Fiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>
