		<title>Love in the Night</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/andy-robertson-s-night-land-essays/173-love-in-the-night"/>
		<published>2015-07-02T21:27:04+00:00</published>
		<updated>2015-07-02T21:27:04+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/andy-robertson-s-night-land-essays/173-love-in-the-night</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;What was Hodgson Attempting in his Treatment of the Erotic in THE NIGHT LAND and THE HOUSE ON THE BORDERLAND?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/173-love-in-the-night&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/fabian-x-and-naani-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A man and a woman embracing; drawing in blue and white&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;article-teaser&quot;&gt;The erotic aspects of Hodgson's work have been universally and justly abused. What on earth was he trying to do?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;What was Hodgson Attempting in his Treatment of the Erotic in THE NIGHT LAND and THE HOUSE ON THE BORDERLAND?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/107-andy-robertson&quot;&gt;Andy Robertson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/background/essays/173-love-in-the-night&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/fabian-x-and-naani-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A man and a woman embracing; drawing in blue and white&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;article-teaser&quot;&gt;The erotic aspects of Hodgson's work have been universally and justly abused. What on earth was he trying to do?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
